sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User Python Code
    participant SDK as TrainerClient SDK
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant TrainerOp as Trainer Operator
    participant JobSet as JobSet Controller
    participant Pod as Training Pod
    participant MetricsSrv as HTTP Metrics Server<br/>(injected by RHAI)
    participant S3 as S3 Object Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant SparkOp as Spark Operator
    participant SparkPod as Spark Driver Pod<br/>15002/TCP gRPC
    participant ModelReg as Model Registry<br/>443/8080 TCP HTTP/HTTPS

    Note over User,S3: Flow 1: Training Job Submission (Kubernetes Backend)
    User->>SDK: trainer.train(train_func, config)
    SDK->>K8sAPI: POST TrainJob CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>TrainerOp: Reconcile TrainJob
    TrainerOp->>JobSet: Create JobSet
    JobSet->>Pod: Schedule training pods
    SDK->>K8sAPI: GET pods/log (stream)<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI-->>SDK: Training logs

    Note over User,S3: Flow 2: RHAI Training with Progression Tracking
    User->>SDK: trainer.train(TransformersTrainer, config)
    SDK->>K8sAPI: POST TrainJob CR<br/>(with instrumented code + annotations)
    K8sAPI->>TrainerOp: Reconcile TrainJob
    TrainerOp->>Pod: Create training pod<br/>(with metrics server injected)
    Pod->>MetricsSrv: Start HTTP server
    TrainerOp->>MetricsSrv: GET /metrics (poll)<br/>HTTP, no encryption
    MetricsSrv-->>TrainerOp: JSON metrics<br/>(progress, ETA, step, loss)
    Pod->>Pod: Write /dev/termination-log<br/>(final metrics)

    Note over User,S3: Flow 3: JIT Checkpoint to S3
    Pod->>Pod: Receive SIGTERM<br/>(preemption/scale-down)
    Pod->>Pod: CheckpointManager saves to<br/>/mnt/kubeflow-checkpoints
    Pod->>S3: Upload checkpoint<br/>fsspec/s3fs<br/>Auth: AWS credentials from Secret
    S3-->>Pod: Upload complete
    Note over Pod: Removes checkpoint-is-incomplete.txt<br/>marker on success

    Note over User,SparkPod: Flow 4: Spark Connect Session
    User->>SDK: spark.create_session(config)
    SDK->>K8sAPI: POST SparkConnect CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>SparkOp: Reconcile SparkConnect
    SparkOp->>SparkPod: Create driver + executor pods
    SDK->>SparkPod: gRPC Connect<br/>15002/TCP, no encryption
    User->>SDK: spark.execute(query)
    SDK->>SparkPod: Spark SQL via gRPC<br/>15002/TCP

    Note over User,ModelReg: Flow 5: Model Registration
    User->>SDK: hub.register_model(model)
    SDK->>ModelReg: POST /api/model_registry<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (optional)<br/>Custom CA (optional)
    ModelReg-->>SDK: Model version registered
